No. If he had that,
he'd be trying to prevent NSYNC

4
00:00:13,757 --> 00:00:15,389
from breaking up.

5
00:00:15,391 --> 00:00:17,125
Oh, please.
I'm glad they broke up.

6
00:00:17,127 --> 00:00:19,828
Otherwise, Justin would
never have brought sexy back.

7
00:00:20,997 --> 00:00:23,397
One thing you can't get
on an iPad,

8
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,967
the smell of ink and paper.

9
00:00:25,970 --> 00:00:28,369
One more reason
iPads are better.

10
00:00:29,939 --> 00:00:31,540
They reviewed
my planetarium show.

11
00:00:31,542 --> 00:00:34,443
Yeah. It's on page three
of the Arts and Leisure section.

12
00:00:42,353 --> 00:00:44,920
Oh, look, they still
have Far Side.

13
00:00:44,922 --> 00:00:46,889
Oh, I don't
get that one.

14
00:00:46,890 --> 00:00:49,758
Oh, he's pushing
when he should be pulling.

15
00:00:49,759 --> 00:00:54,096
Hmm. I don't think he belongs
in that gifted school, then.

16
00:00:54,097 --> 00:00:55,898
What are you doing?
Making a boat.

17
00:00:55,899 --> 00:00:57,999
When I was a kid,
my dad showed me how.

18
00:00:58,002 --> 00:01:00,868
Boy, you'll do anything
to avoid reading.

19
00:01:02,206 --> 00:01:04,206
Guys, it's under
“Things to do this weekend.”

20
00:01:04,207 --> 00:01:06,008
I can't find it.
What does it say?

21
00:01:06,009 --> 00:01:09,277
That it's a thing
to do this weekend.

22
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:12,080
That's great, Raj.
Congratulations.

23
00:01:12,081 --> 00:01:13,247
You know, while we're bragging,

24
00:01:13,250 --> 00:01:14,883
The Journal
of Prosthetic Medicine

25
00:01:14,884 --> 00:01:17,119
just wrote up the project that
Howard and I are working on.

26
00:01:17,121 --> 00:01:19,253
Well, you didn't
tell me that.

27
00:01:19,256 --> 00:01:21,490
Oh, it just came out.
It's just a little blurb.

28
00:01:21,491 --> 00:01:23,559
Oh, well, good for you.

29
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:25,794
You know, Bert and I have
started isolating zircons

30
00:01:25,795 --> 00:01:28,262
from meteorites
for our dark matter search.

31
00:01:28,264 --> 00:01:29,631
Oh. Well, how nice.

32
00:01:29,633 --> 00:01:31,066
Everyone's doing
impressive work.

33
00:01:31,068 --> 00:01:32,800
What have you been
working on these days?

34
00:01:32,803 --> 00:01:35,603
Whoa, whoa. Where'd
that come from?

35
00:01:35,606 --> 00:01:37,673
Where did what come from?

36
00:01:37,675 --> 00:01:38,973
I try to be supportive,

37
00:01:38,976 --> 00:01:42,377
and you break out the hot
lights and the rubber hose.

38
00:01:42,378 --> 00:01:44,045
I just asked
what you've been working on.

39
00:01:44,048 --> 00:01:46,014
Oh, my God, let it go.

40
00:01:46,015 --> 00:01:47,482
Do you believe this guy?

41
00:01:47,484 --> 00:01:50,285
I did it!

42
00:01:51,822 --> 00:01:54,756
See? It's a... it's a boat.

43
00:01:56,459 --> 00:02:00,127
It's also a hat.

44
